1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,840
Wad, we're in trouble.
The governor's men are raiding Chum Suea.

2
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,360
Burn Chum Suea to the ground!

3
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:12,280
- Dad!
- <i>Masa namo.</i>

4
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,080
Chum Suea is finished.

5
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,080
Huh?

6
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:19,320
Wad! Why did you kill him?

7
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:22,360
I'm going to skin you

8
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,040
and make a tattooed jacket out of it.

9
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:28,000
I told you to stab his anus!

10
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,080
Dad!

11
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:32,560
<i>Phutthang chivitang yawa nippanang.</i>

12
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,960
<i>If you two have fate together…</i>

13
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,640
Forgive me, Yod.

14
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,440
I came too late.

15
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,640
I couldn't save you or your family.

16
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,080
Who the hell are you?

17
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:58,280
So you're about to ordain? Guess I should
get ready to pay my respects.

18
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:07,480
Who are you, to dare show up
before the Buddha?

19
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,760
Don't go to Khao Phrom.

20
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,200
It's pointless.

21
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,920
Believe me.

22
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,280
I'm going. No one can stop me.

23
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,320
Even if you go,

24
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:35,560
it's not like they'll teach you sorcery.

25
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,800
I have a letter of admission
from the governor.

26
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,480
They'll have to accept me.

27
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,120
Fine. Suit yourself.

28
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:51,680
Lasor, have you forgotten already?

29
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,680
Your father wants you to ordain.

30
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:55,760
Huh?

31
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,960
Lasor.

32
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,120
<i>Manusso si…</i>

33
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,040
<i>Ama bhante…</i>

34
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,560
Your father wants you to ordain.

35
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,640
Your father wants you to ordain.

36
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,120
<i>Manusso si. Ama bhante.</i>

37
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,560
<i>Yiam.</i>

38
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,320
<i>Yiam.</i>

39
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,000
<i>Yiam.</i>

40
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,160
<i>Yiam.</i>

41
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,920
Dad. Mom.

42
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,760
Sleep here tonight, Yiam.

43
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:58,120
No matter what you hear or see,
do not come out

44
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,360
until dawn.

45
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,040
Why?

46
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:05,200
Just do as I say.

47
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,720
<i>Yiam.</i>

48
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,440
<i>Come see me.</i>

49
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,720
<i>Come to me, my son.</i>

50
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,960
Dad.

51
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,480
Mom.

52
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,080
Yam.

53
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,680
We've come to take you with us.

54
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,640
Let's go home.

55
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,560
Yiam, I want to hear Phra Aphai Mani.

56
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:29,360
<i>Never trust mankind.</i>

57
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:35,000
<i>Their depths are endless, beyond measure.</i>

58
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:40,480
<i>Even twisting vines</i>

59
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:45,880
<i>are not as crooked as the human heart.</i>

60
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,320
Come with us, Yiam.

61
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,560
I missed you beyond words.

62
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:06,680
I want to be with you.
Please stay with me.

63
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,440
Where are you going?

64
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,200
What was that, Master?

65
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,440
What you saw

66
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,760
was created by your own mind.

67
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,440
When it appears again,

68
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:27,160
stay focused, and it will fade.

69
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,680
Is that the spirit
of my father, my mother,

70
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,840
and my little sister, Master?

71
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,360
No.

72
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:46,480
Everything arises, exists, and ceases.

73
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,720
Nothing lasts forever.

74
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,080
Everything will be gone one day.

75
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,800
If you still cling to them,

76
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,960
you will never be free from suffering.

77
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,400
Master, I wish to learn sorcery.

78
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,800
For what purpose?

79
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,240
So I can…

80
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:24,000
take revenge.

81
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,920
I will teach you medicine.

82
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:36,040
That is no longer what I wish to learn.

83
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,400
Dawn is breaking.

84
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:46,600
Go gather herbs for the medicine.

85
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,200
But…

86
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:22,120
Lasor, I've prepared everything
for your ordination.

87
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,520
Lasor.

88
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:36,520
Nui.

89
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,360
You've gone too far to turn back now,

90
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,360
Lasor.

91
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:54,400
You should've stayed
to say goodbye to Father Wad.

92
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,800
If Dad saw me, he'd never let me leave.

93
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,160
But he truly wanted you to ordain.

94
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,920
Even if I did, I'd disrobe anyway.

95
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,720
The robe would burn. I'd leave in the end.

96
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:10,920
After you learn sorcery at Khao Phrom,

97
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,120
what will you do?

98
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,680
I'll make Dad acknowledge me.

99
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,720
Nui,

100
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,200
did you hear that?

101
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,360
Hear what?

102
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,680
I only hear crows.

103
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:12,920
Wait for me here.

104
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:13,920
Okay.

105
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,840
- Who are you here for?
- Hey!

106
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:49,960
Hey?!

107
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:58,880
Are you trying to kill me?

108
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:03,200
You came out of nowhere.
I had to protect myself.

109
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,720
Are you Yiwha?

110
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:14,120
This is Chaem,
another one of your father's friends.

111
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,800
They studied at Khao Phrom together.

112
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,240
Greetings, Uncle Chaem.

113
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,880
So you know
this skull-kicking wild mare too?

114
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,920
What's going on?

115
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,480
Yod is dead,

116
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,320
and Wad's Chum Suea
was completely wiped out.

117
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,800
It's not safe there anymore.

118
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:52,080
So Wad asked me to bring his daughter here
to stay with you in Huai Yao for a while.

119
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:58,280
Make yourself at home.
Just think of this place as your own.

120
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,800
You can even stay here
for the rest of your life.

121
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,280
Thanks, Chaem.

122
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:07,839
That's what friends do. We look out for
each other when everything goes to hell.

123
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,000
Here, have some hot rice porridge.

124
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,160
- Niem.
- Yeah?

125
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,400
I've prepared bedding for you.

126
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:37,240
As for Yiwha, you'll sleep
in the same room as Noree, my niece.

127
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,920
If you need anything, tell Chang.

128
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,200
Yes.

129
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:49,840
Oh, Pun. What brings you here?

130
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,440
I brought <i>zongzi</i> for you.

131
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:55,720
Come in.

132
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,880
Thanks.

133
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,640
Here, eat this.

134
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,240
Alright.

135
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,120
Have you heard any news about Yiam?

136
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,000
The police still haven't found his body.

137
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,920
Maybe he's not dead yet.

138
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,200
If I ever become a police officer,

139
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,600
I'll investigate the case

140
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,680
and get justice for Yiam.

141
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:57,560
Chang,

142
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,120
who's that woman?

143
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,120
My Dad's friend's daughter.
Her name's Yiwha.

144
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:07,520
Why? Are you interested?

145
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,840
She's pretty. And cute.

146
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:13,760
Alright.

147
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,600
I'll introduce you to her.

148
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,080
But I'll warn you.

149
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,040
She's not ordinary.

150
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,360
Pun.

151
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:31,920
Noree.

152
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,600
Your true match is right here.

153
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:40,040
Where'd you go?

154
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,880
I went to the market to buy vegetables.

155
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:11,840
I've gathered
the medicinal herbs for you, Master.

156
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:15,080
What did you get?

157
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:22,840
Wild cardamom, for severe fever,
bloating, indigestion,

158
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:25,960
colic, urinary disorders.

159
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:31,680
‪Rang Jued is used to detoxify poisons.

160
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:34,200
It reduces fever
and relieves swelling and pain.

161
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,960
This wild krawan leaf
can't be used yet. It's rotten.

162
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,640
Rotten herbs like these

163
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:58,000
are like a restless mind,

164
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,280
unsettled,

165
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:02,560
useless.

166
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:07,040
Worse, they can even cause harm.

167
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,280
Master,

168
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,080
I want to learn sorcery.

169
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,160
Please have mercy and teach me.

170
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:36,640
Tomorrow, go gather them again.

171
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:38,680
But…

172
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,280
You still won't tell me your name?

173
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:44,120
My name is Orror, Blur.

174
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,200
So we're just going to
keep calling each other that forever?

175
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:54,360
It doesn't matter what our names are.

176
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:57,680
As long as I'm me, and you're you.

177
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:59,400
That's enough.

178
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,680
I don't know your name.

179
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:06,960
I don't know where you live.

180
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:10,480
So if one day you disappear,

181
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:12,720
how would I ever find you?

182
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,680
Even if the world is vast,

183
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:22,280
our hearts will find each other.

184
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,480
I'll trust you, Orror.

185
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:55,600
One day, we'll find
our way back to each other.

186
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,760
- Hey, Pun.
- Hm?

187
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:07,080
How's your father's shop doing?

188
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,560
Same as always.

189
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:12,280
My dad still wants me
to take over the business.

190
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:15,160
I told him I don't want to,
but he never listens.

191
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:19,160
I stitched the tear in your shirt.

192
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,360
Thanks, Noree.

193
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:28,880
I embroidered this handkerchief for you.

194
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,560
- Thank you, Noree.
- You're welcome.

195
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:37,760
I feel bad taking it.

196
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,000
Yiwha.

197
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:53,720
Noree, this is Yiwha, Uncle Niem's niece.

198
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:56,600
She'll be staying with us.
You should get to know each other.

199
00:24:58,040 --> 00:24:59,240
I'm Yiwha.

200
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,360
I'm Noree.

201
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,200
Wow. It's so pretty.

202
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:09,160
Did you embroider it yourself?

203
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,520
Can you teach me sometime?

204
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,560
What flower is that? It's beautiful.

205
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:22,520
A peony.

206
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:27,040
Chinese people believe

207
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,480
- it represents--
- Love.

208
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,400
Chinese people say peonies

209
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:44,880
symbolize good fortune and wealth.

210
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,600
It's beautiful,
and the meaning is lovely too.

211
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,720
Anyone who receives it
would surely be happy.

212
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:54,600
Right?

213
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:56,520
Yes.

214
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:12,040
- I like Yiwha.
- Huh?

215
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:17,240
You just met her once
and you're already into her?

216
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:20,360
Yiwha is the one I've been looking for.

217
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,240
And what about Noree?

218
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,040
You know that.

219
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:28,880
I see her like a little sister.
I've never thought of her that way.

220
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,120
I don't want to see her get hurt.

221
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:38,080
Noree is like my real sister.

222
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:40,960
Chang, you have to help me.

223
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:44,480
Help you with what?

224
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:46,160
Help me to end up with Yiwha.

225
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,120
You've got to be kidding.

226
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,760
Help me, please.

227
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,320
Please, Chang, my best friend!

228
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,160
Help me, please.

229
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:56,720
Please.

230
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:19,800
Do you like Pun?

231
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:26,920
I…

232
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,240
We're both girls. Don't be shy.

233
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:44,240
But Pun doesn't feel that way about me.

234
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,960
Why not?

235
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:49,040
You're pretty,

236
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:51,680
and you're good at housework too.

237
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:53,520
I can't compare to you.

238
00:27:56,520 --> 00:28:00,240
I'm an orphan Uncle Chaem took in.
No one would ever care about me.

239
00:28:12,280 --> 00:28:13,640
You want me to help?

240
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,320
Help?

241
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,880
Help you end up with Pun.

242
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:49,560
Your plan was incredible, Pud.

243
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:53,560
You tricked them into killing each other.

244
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:58,840
And you even got the authorities
to declare Bandit Wad an enemy.

245
00:28:58,920 --> 00:28:59,800
Brilliant.

246
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:04,240
Now Khun Yod has been dealt with.

247
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,840
Only Wad is left.

248
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:09,520
I've sent my men to hunt him down.

249
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,680
If they can't take him alive, kill him.

250
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,960
Bandit Wad can't have gotten far.

251
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,920
As for his son, Lasor,

252
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,160
I've sent men to wait at Khao Phrom.

253
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:22,400
The moment he arrives,
we'll clap him in stocks immediately.

254
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,000
Don't let him escape again.

255
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:27,040
Yes, sir.

256
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,680
Once we catch Lasor,

257
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:31,160
luring his father out won't be hard.

258
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:33,600
Wad will come for his son.

259
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:38,840
When we catch Bandit Wad,

260
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,200
I'll chop him into 10,000 pieces.

261
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:43,200
Then I'll be satisfied.

262
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:49,520
And Bandit Wad's men
the police captured, sir?

263
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,320
Hang them.

264
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:58,520
Yes, sir.

265
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:27,360
Nightmare, Lasor?

266
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:31,520
Yeah.

267
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:35,840
What did you dream about?

268
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:47,800
Nothing. Forget it. Sleep.

269
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:51,400
Okay. I'll go back to sleep then.

270
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,000
<i>Rotten herbs like these</i>

271
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,960
<i>are like a restless mind,</i>

272
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:21,240
<i>unsettled, useless.</i>

273
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,880
<i>Worse, they can even cause harm.</i>

274
00:32:07,320 --> 00:32:10,960
No matter what you hear or see,
do not come out.

275
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:12,560
Not until morning.

276
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,480
Ylang-ylang helps ease dizziness,

277
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,040
strengthens the heart,

278
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:02,560
and helps with urinary trouble.

279
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:05,720
Black lily, or <i>neraphoosi,</i>

280
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:08,040
used to nourish
and support pregnant women.

281
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,840
I sorted only fresh herbs.

282
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:14,040
Not even a trace of rot.

283
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,600
Good.

284
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:28,840
Keep doing it. Make it a habit.

285
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:33,240
Master.

286
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:40,120
Please show me mercy and teach me sorcery.

287
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,400
Every herb

288
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,760
has its proper time.

289
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:54,200
Some must be picked late, some early.

290
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,080
Some in summer,

291
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,480
some in the rainy season,

292
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:02,080
some in winter.

293
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:04,440
Some by day,

294
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:07,440
some by night.

295
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:10,400
It depends on what is appropriate.

296
00:34:13,159 --> 00:34:14,760
But Master,

297
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,840
I have to learn sorcery.

298
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:31,360
Someone is here to see you, Master.

299
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:37,360
Let him in.

300
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,880
Tomorrow, go gather them again.

301
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:25,080
The Master allows you to go in.

302
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:29,120
Wait here, Nui. Don't follow me in.

303
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:30,920
Okay.

304
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:39,920
If those two meet, will it be all right?

305
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:44,440
Khao Phrom is sacred ground.

306
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:47,080
No one may fight to the death here.

307
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:33,600
I can't take you as my disciple.

308
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:35,840
GOVERNOR OF THA KHIRI

309
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:54,800
Venerable sir,

310
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:59,080
I have a letter of introduction
from the Governor.

311
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,600
Why won't you accept me?

312
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:07,320
I teach sorcery
only to those I am able to teach.

313
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:10,880
I'll study hard.

314
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:13,920
I'll remember every word you teach.

315
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,280
Whatever you tell me to do,

316
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:18,960
I'll do it all.

317
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:26,840
All beings follow their own karma.

318
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:29,440
Go your own way.

319
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:39,960
What do you mean?

320
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,400
You're a monk.

321
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,520
You're supposed to help people!

322
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:50,560
The Master won't teach you. Leave.

323
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,840
Stay out of it.

324
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:58,000
I hacked my way
through the jungle to get here,

325
00:37:58,080 --> 00:38:00,120
and you're just
sending me back this easily?

326
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,520
If you keep being stubborn,

327
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:04,960
I'll have people drag you out.

328
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,800
I'm asking one last time.

329
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:24,360
Will you teach me or not?

330
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,520
You think I don't dare?

331
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,960
Go back.

332
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:49,080
I will confess an offense.

333
00:39:08,760 --> 00:39:11,680
Lasor,
did Old Master Khrua Phut accept you?

334
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:14,320
He's guarding his knowledge.
He won't teach me.

335
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:17,640
Huh? But everyone says he's compassionate.

336
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:22,080
Nui, don't say his name again.
Let's go back.

337
00:39:22,680 --> 00:39:23,960
Alright.

338
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:25,600
Where are you rushing off to, Lasor?

339
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,200
I'm not going!

340
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,280
Die!

341
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:41,080
Lasor, run!

342
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:48,680
- Go after them!
- Go!

343
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,920
What do we do now?

344
00:39:58,640 --> 00:39:59,840
You won't get away now.

345
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,880
Worst case, we die.

346
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:12,480
- Ugh!
- Brother!

347
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:13,680
You!

348
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:19,000
Nui.

349
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,040
Nui.

350
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,400
- Die!
- No, you die!

351
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:50,320
Push the needle up,

352
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:52,000
loop the thread into a circle,

353
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,560
then go back down in the same spot.

354
00:40:56,480 --> 00:41:00,160
Pull it tight.
Run the stitch under the fabric.

355
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:03,520
Push the needle up.

356
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,400
Try it.

357
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,400
Push the needle down.

358
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:14,160
Yeah, push the needle up.
Loop the thread into a circle.

359
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:16,440
Loop the thread into a circle.

360
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:20,800
Yes, and go back down in the same spot.

361
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:23,720
Do it again.

362
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:25,520
‪Alright.

363
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,880
Then pull it tight.

364
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:30,000
Run the stitch under the fabric.

365
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:32,400
Run the stitch under the fabric.

366
00:41:32,920 --> 00:41:34,280
- Run--
- Ugh.

367
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:35,520
This is hard.

368
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,480
Throwing knives is way easier.

369
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:41,880
You can throw knives?

370
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:44,520
Can you teach me?

371
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:47,360
Sure. I'll teach you.

372
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:48,800
Okay.

373
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,960
Pun, did you come to see Uncle Chaem?

374
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:03,200
Well, I…

375
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,080
I…

376
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,800
He wants to ask Yiwha
to go for a walk at the market.

377
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:16,680
Come with me, Yiwha.

378
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:20,600
Sure.

379
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:23,840
Come on, Noree. Let's go to the market.

380
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,840
Here are some vegetables.
What would you like?

381
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,160
Huai Yao's a small district,
nothing like the bustle of Tha Khiri.

382
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,080
You must be bored here.

383
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:13,600
Then you should take Yiwha out
for walks often, so she won't get bored.

384
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:18,800
I won't be bored.
I've got Noree as a friend.

385
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,840
There's a lot we want to do together.

386
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:25,600
So what do you like doing?
Making flower garlands?

387
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:29,800
Sewing? Cooking?

388
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:31,400
Ah.

389
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:35,800
Everything you just said,
I can't do a single one of.

390
00:43:38,120 --> 00:43:40,880
Then you must like dressing up.

391
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:42,520
Perfect.

392
00:43:43,200 --> 00:43:45,920
Pun's father is a big merchant here.

393
00:43:46,760 --> 00:43:49,280
Let him take you to his store sometime.

394
00:43:50,080 --> 00:43:52,880
There are lots of pretty things for women.

395
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:57,800
I don't like dressing up.

396
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:59,760
I don't like makeup or lipstick.

397
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:02,280
And I don't like perfume
or scented oils either.

398
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:05,640
Then what do you like?

399
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,040
I like…

400
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:15,640
throwing knives.

401
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:22,000
Oh.

402
00:44:22,720 --> 00:44:24,760
I've been wanting to ask you.

403
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:28,160
Did your dad teach you to throw knives?

404
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:32,640
That's wild. I've never seen
a father teach his daughter that.

405
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:34,800
Uncle Niem taught me.

406
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:38,680
My dad doesn't like me
doing stuff like that.

407
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:43,400
All my stuff is ruined!

408
00:44:43,480 --> 00:44:44,680
So what?

409
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:48,120
Are you going to pay
the easy way, or the hard way?

410
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:50,400
I really don't have anything, Saeng.

411
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:53,600
I haven't sold a thing this morning.

412
00:44:56,400 --> 00:44:57,720
Don't have?

413
00:45:00,160 --> 00:45:02,720
Then sell your daughter to me.

414
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:04,040
No.

415
00:45:04,120 --> 00:45:06,520
She's still young. Please, have mercy.

416
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:08,320
Don't take her.

417
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:10,320
- You're so tough, huh?
- Mom!

418
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:12,480
- Help me!
- Stop screaming!

419
00:45:12,560 --> 00:45:13,520
You wanna get slapped?

420
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:15,600
Picking on women and kids?

421
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:17,760
Real men don't do that.

422
00:45:20,280 --> 00:45:21,640
It's none of your business.

423
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:28,000
Saeng's Khun Paeng's man.
Don't mess with them.

424
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:33,760
You're with the authorities and you think
you can bully villagers however you want?

425
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,160
Hey.

426
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:39,120
Teach this mouthy bitch a lesson.

427
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:42,480
Yes.

428
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,560
I'll protect you, Yiwha.

429
00:45:48,240 --> 00:45:49,240
Hey.

430
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:16,200
Saeng pissed himself.

431
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:18,960
Saeng pissed himself!

432
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:22,880
- He pissed himself.
- Look.

433
00:46:22,960 --> 00:46:25,160
Saeng pissed himself.

434
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:26,920
This isn't over yet.

435
00:46:27,560 --> 00:46:30,200
- Let's go.
- Go.

436
00:46:37,160 --> 00:46:39,160
Thank you so much.

437
00:46:39,240 --> 00:46:40,640
Thank you.

438
00:46:40,720 --> 00:46:42,440
It's good you're safe.

439
00:46:44,680 --> 00:46:45,600
Yiwha.

440
00:46:54,240 --> 00:46:55,360
Uncle Niem.

441
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:01,840
I told you, didn't I?
Not to go out and stir up trouble.

442
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:03,600
I didn't start it.

443
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:05,480
They did.

444
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:06,600
You're talking back?

445
00:47:08,680 --> 00:47:11,360
They were bullying people
who couldn't fight back.

446
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:13,480
How could I just stand there?

447
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:15,880
We have to help people in trouble.

448
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:18,520
- You taught me that.
- Talking back?

449
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:20,920
Don't run!

450
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:22,560
Uncle Niem,

451
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:25,040
Saeng started it with the vendor first.

452
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:27,280
Yiwha just went in to help.

453
00:47:27,360 --> 00:47:30,440
It's true, Uncle.
I saw it with my own eyes.

454
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:33,120
Alright, alright. It's done.

455
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:35,480
Let's talk about what to do next.

456
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:40,200
Saeng's close to Tim.

457
00:47:41,240 --> 00:47:43,360
By now he's probably run back
to report to his boss.

458
00:48:02,680 --> 00:48:03,640
Dad,

459
00:48:04,520 --> 00:48:05,760
can I ask you something?

460
00:48:08,120 --> 00:48:08,960
Mm.

461
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:12,320
Who exactly is Yiwha?

462
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:16,520
She's Niem's niece.

463
00:48:17,320 --> 00:48:18,840
Come on, Dad.

464
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:23,240
Don't play dumb.
What kind of woman is that skilled?

465
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:26,440
Yeah, I watched her throw knives
right at Saeng's men.

466
00:48:27,040 --> 00:48:28,000
Even I was stunned.

467
00:48:28,080 --> 00:48:31,280
Right. Who is Yiwha's family?

468
00:48:40,280 --> 00:48:42,200
If I tell you, keep your mouths shut.

469
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:53,080
Yiwha is Bandit Wad's daughter.

470
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:54,520
Huh?

471
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:57,560
Bandit Wad?

472
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:01,440
The one they're hunting
for killing Khun Yod's whole family?

473
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:05,120
Then that means

474
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:07,240
Bandit Wad has two kids,

475
00:49:07,320 --> 00:49:09,040
Yiwha and Lasor.

476
00:49:09,120 --> 00:49:11,240
So Yiwha's the daughter
of a bandit-murderer.

477
00:49:11,320 --> 00:49:12,560
Don't jump to conclusions.

478
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:16,080
Something about this is off.

479
00:49:16,680 --> 00:49:19,920
Bandit Wad and Khun Yod
were fellow disciples at Khao Phrom.

480
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:24,000
There's no way Bandit Wad killed Khun Yod.

481
00:49:24,600 --> 00:49:26,440
Friends kill friends all the time.

482
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:28,600
How do you know he didn't?

483
00:49:29,240 --> 00:49:31,920
Because Niem and I are his friends too.

484
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:44,360
Come in.

485
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:53,400
This cave stores the collected scriptures

486
00:49:53,480 --> 00:49:55,320
of all disciplines

487
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:56,760
taught at Khao Phrom,

488
00:49:56,840 --> 00:49:59,960
medical texts, astrology manuals,

489
00:50:00,040 --> 00:50:01,920
and texts of sorcery.

490
00:50:03,440 --> 00:50:04,720
Sorcery?

491
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:07,680
Not everyone is allowed to enter this cave

492
00:50:07,760 --> 00:50:09,520
Only those granted permission
by the Master.

493
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:13,200
Absorb whatever knowledge you can,

494
00:50:13,280 --> 00:50:15,520
according to the limits
of your own wisdom.

495
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:46,760
Nui.

496
00:51:48,240 --> 00:51:49,240
Nui, wake up.

497
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:51,880
Nui.

498
00:51:52,600 --> 00:51:53,520
Wake up.

499
00:52:03,560 --> 00:52:04,440
Nui.

500
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:21,880
Brother.

501
00:52:24,080 --> 00:52:26,240
How did we end up here?

502
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:35,520
I don't know either.

503
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:47,560
Nui,

504
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:51,640
I'll go find Siam weed leaves
to stop the bleeding. Wait here.

505
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:54,440
Brother…

506
00:52:54,520 --> 00:52:56,040
Brother.

507
00:52:58,000 --> 00:52:59,360
Don't leave me.

508
00:53:03,080 --> 00:53:04,080
Nui,

509
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:07,760
you're like my own little brother.

510
00:53:08,520 --> 00:53:09,960
I'd never leave you.

511
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:30,760
Whose laughter is that?

512
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:36,200
You heard it too?

513
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:49,760
Come on, Nui. I know how to save you now.

514
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:52,480
- Let's go.
- Okay.

515
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,400
Slowly.

516
00:54:02,280 --> 00:54:04,680
Hang in there.

517
00:54:04,760 --> 00:54:07,560
Come on.

518
00:54:22,160 --> 00:54:23,280
Where are you?

519
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:28,720
At last,

520
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:31,240
you've come to me.

521
00:54:37,720 --> 00:54:41,080
A ghost? Is he a ghost?

522
00:54:44,240 --> 00:54:45,200
No.

523
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:47,920
He's not a ghost.

524
00:54:49,560 --> 00:54:51,000
How do you know?

525
00:54:52,440 --> 00:54:54,000
I think I've met him before.

526
00:54:55,600 --> 00:54:57,480
If you're really brave,

527
00:54:58,720 --> 00:55:00,880
then come closer to me.

528
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:05,840
Nui,

529
00:55:07,400 --> 00:55:08,800
wait for me here.

530
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:13,600
Slowly.

531
00:55:30,240 --> 00:55:31,360
Lasor.

532
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:51,240
If you're going to kill someone, kill me.

533
00:55:52,560 --> 00:55:53,840
But let my brother go.

534
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:02,520
You want to learn sorcery
so badly, don't you?

535
00:56:03,520 --> 00:56:05,080
I'll teach you myself.

536
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,520
I'll teach you myself.

537
00:56:23,560 --> 00:56:25,240
Yiwha said she was going to
look for her brother.

538
00:56:25,320 --> 00:56:27,240
That's asking for trouble.

539
00:56:27,320 --> 00:56:28,880
I'm sorry, Uncle Niem.

540
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:31,840
<i>I just want to see Lasor once.</i>

541
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:34,520
A ghost?!

542
00:56:34,600 --> 00:56:37,000
- <i>How did you get here?</i>
- <i>Do you miss me?</i>

543
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:39,400
Yod's talisman? Did you kill Yod?

544
00:56:39,480 --> 00:56:41,120
Why wouldn't I kill someone like him?

545
00:56:41,200 --> 00:56:43,040
<i>Etesang sappayaka…</i>

546
00:56:43,120 --> 00:56:45,120
<i>I never trusted them.</i>

547
00:56:45,200 --> 00:56:46,840
You mean Khun Paeng or Bandit Pud?

548
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:48,200
Both of them.

549
00:56:50,960 --> 00:56:53,240
I need something for my offering.

550
00:56:53,320 --> 00:56:55,680
- What is it?
- His life.

551
00:56:57,320 --> 00:57:00,280
You still won't abandon the idea
of going back for revenge?

552
00:57:00,360 --> 00:57:03,280
<i>My suffering will only end,</i>

553
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:05,880
<i>when they face</i>
<i>the consequences of their karma.</i>

554
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:07,560
You killed my family.

555
00:57:07,640 --> 00:57:10,600
Finally, we met.

556
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:11,720
Come on!

557
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:15,000
Hey!

558
00:57:58,680 --> 00:58:01,400
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
